您加入频道时，您都会看到一系列类似的公共频道。 Telegram 根据用户群的相似性提出这些建议。您可以随时前往频道的个人资料查看这些推荐。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/a9447280-9076-11ee-9377-f4a160c67fae" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/a9447280-9076-11ee-9377-f4a160c67fae" style="height:1600px;width:1920px;" alt="一个圆形图标显示一群朋友低头对着相机镜头挥手。该图像覆盖在移动应用程序中的多风海滩上。文字阅读" data-uuid="5b36b166-d1e0-36b8-8f9e-f19b8e9145c2"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">电报</div></figure><p>您现在可以在故事中添加视频评论或反应。您将能够调整该视频消息的大小并在屏幕上移动它。您可以添加视频消息，这是一项借鉴<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/tiktok/">TikTok</a>剧本的功能，只需按住故事编辑器中的相机图标即可捕捉自拍照片段。您可以通过将手指放在屏幕底部的视频轨道上来调节音量。</p><p>转发别人的故事现在也轻而易举。只需点击故事上的分享按钮，您就可以选择重新发布它。只有公开可见性的故事才能重新发布。您也可以为转发的故事添加视频评论。</p><p>在其他地方，高级用户可以使用独特的颜色组合设置他们的个人资料，每个人都可以将自定义壁纸应用于每个单独的聊天（高级用户可以为两个参与者设置相同的壁纸），频道管理员可以自定义显示为反应的表情符号。此外，任何 Telegram 应用程序现在都可以检测消息中的编码语言，并以正确的格式突出显示语法。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/telegram-now-offers-all-users-limited-transcriptions-of-voice-messages-185114448.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/telegram-now-offers-all-users-limited-transcriptions-of-voice-messages-185114448.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 08e4c23a-1189-4225-a9be-72eff26aea64</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 01 Dec 2023 18:51:14 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701456674</ingested><modified> 2023-12-01T18:51:21+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Small Businesses]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="915" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F0dc9eff0-9077-11ee-bf9f-8bc3be8a9dfe&amp;resize=1400%2C915&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=4afb2b2cff5c337f586e94c38b4ae61c62ca36e1" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="915" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F0dc9eff0-9077-11ee-bf9f-8bc3be8a9dfe&amp;resize=1400%2C915&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=271f1fca2df4b92eb8fcdc2e698d06d1fef92e0b" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Telegram]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A screenshot of a private conversation on the Telegram app. On the left is a voice message which includes a transcription underneath.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[A screenshot of a private conversation on the Telegram app. On the left is a voice message which includes a transcription underneath.]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Researchers quantify the carbon footprint of generating AI images]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>人工智能初创公司<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://huggingface.co/">Hugging Face</a>的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2311.16863.pdf">研究人员</a>与卡内基梅隆大学合作，发现使用人工智能<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/blender-can-now-use-ai-to-create-images-and-effects-from-text-descriptions-175001548.html">生成图像</a>，无论是创建<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/shutterstock-ai-generated-stock-images-dall-e-133903619.html">库存图像</a>还是<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ai-can-produce-detailed-photos-of-faces-from-simple-sketches-122924655.html">真实的身份证照片</a>，其碳足迹相当于为智能手机充电。然而，研究人员发现，生成文本，无论是<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-messages-now-lets-you-choose-your-own-chat-bubble-colors-170042264.html">与聊天机器人进行对话</a>还是清理文章，所需的能量都比生成照片少得多。研究人员量化了人工智能生成的文本所消耗的能量，相当于将智能手机充电至充满电的 16% 所消耗的能量。</p><p>这项研究不仅仅研究机器学习程序生成图像和文本。研究人员总共检查了从摘要到文本分类的 13 项任务，并测量了每 1000 克产生的二氧化碳量。为了保持研究的公平性和数据集的多样性，研究人员表示，他们使用 30 个数据集在 88 个不同的模型上进行了实验。对于每项任务，研究人员都会运行 1,000 个提示，同时收集“碳代码”，以测量交换期间消耗的能源和碳排放。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/9a14fb60-906f-11ee-b9fa-fb60c31fc38c" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/9a14fb60-906f-11ee-b9fa-fb60c31fc38c" style="height:1308px;width:2818px;" alt="研究图表" data-uuid="65fc25ac-6fe3-32ec-82ad-38d6fc7b4feb"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">拥抱脸/卡内基梅隆大学</div></figure><p>研究结果强调，最耗能的任务是那些要求人工智能模型生成新内容的任务，无论是文本生成、摘要、图像字幕还是图像生成。图像生成在其产生的排放量方面排名最高，文本分类被列为能耗最低的任务。</p><p>研究人员敦促机器学习科学家和从业者“在其模型的性质和影响方面保持透明度，以便更好地了解其环境影响。”虽然每生成一张人工智能图像为智能手机充电所产生的能源消耗似乎并不可怕，但考虑到人工智能模型的流行和公共化，排放量很容易就会增加。以 ChatGPT 为例，该研究的作者指出，在巅峰时期，OpenAI 的聊天机器人每天拥有超过 1000 万用户，如今<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/how-openais-chatgpt-has-changed-the-world-in-just-a-year-140050053.html">每月有 1 亿活跃用户</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/researchers-quantify-the-carbon-footprint-of-geneating-ai-images-173538174.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/researchers-quantify-the-carbon-footprint-of-generating-ai-images-173538174.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> dc6b2be2-b25e-41f6-900d-2c018db57512</guid><dc:creator>马拉克·萨利赫</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 01 Dec 2023 17:35:38 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701452569</ingested><modified> 2023-12-01T17:42:52+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Environment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nature & Environment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Malak Saleh]]></category><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fd7b093e0-906e-11ee-8dff-d3bdba9bf0b2&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=bb9f5e8780e5a23aae85dc5dcf56bf9e1fd863fa" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fd7b093e0-906e-11ee-8dff-d3bdba9bf0b2&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=ef10397ddee70b7ed601ee488ee533b990d4ef08" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[AP]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The both for Chinese artificial intelligence company Sensetime demonstrates its AI-generated images during the World AI Conference in Shanghai, Wednesday, July 5, 2023. SenseTime, a major Chinese artificial intelligence company known for its facial recognition technology, has rejected claims by a research 